abstract: Labour’s most left-wing leader in a generation suffered a crushing defeat, leaving his party questioning where it heads next.
snippet: Labour’s most left-wing leader in a generation suffered a crushing defeat, leaving his party questioning where it heads next.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — It was supposed to be a new dawn, the moment when Jeremy Corbyn, Britain’s most left-wing political leader in a generation or more, proclaimed the start of the most ambitious economic transformation the nation had seen since the end of World War II.

abstract: United States forward Megan Rapinoe threw her political support behind Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren on Friday, with the two-time World Cup winner announcing she was endorsing the senator amid a tight primary race.
snippet: United States forward Megan Rapinoe threw her political support behind Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren on Friday, with the two-time World Cup winner announcing she was endorsing the senator amid a tight primary race.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - United States forward Megan Rapinoe threw her political support behind Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren on Friday, with the two-time World Cup winner announcing she was endorsing the senator amid a tight primary race.
headline_main: Rapinoe Kicks 2020 Into Gear With Endorsement of Democrat Warren
headline_print_headline: Rapinoe Kicks 2020 Into Gear With Endorsement of Democrat Warren

abstract: The 2016 Brexit vote seemed to be a harbinger of President Trump’s election. But Boris Johnson’s victory may be different.
snippet: The 2016 Brexit vote seemed to be a harbinger of President Trump’s election. But Boris Johnson’s victory may be different.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain was still counting the final votes in its landmark election early Friday morning when Democrats and Republicans on the other side of the Atlantic began asking what Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s landslide victory meant for them: Was it a good omen for President Trump’s re-election chances in 2020, a cautionary tale for Democrats, or both?

headline_main: In Johnson Victory, Democrats and Republicans See Lessons for 2020
headline_print_headline: In Johnson Victory, Democrats and Republicans See Lessons for 2020

abstract: Boris Johnson’s resounding victory means Britain will almost certainly leave the European Union. But what will become of Scotland and Northern Ireland?
snippet: Boris Johnson’s resounding victory means Britain will almost certainly leave the European Union. But what will become of Scotland and Northern Ireland?
lead_paragraph: Of all the agonizing twists and turns of British politics since the narrow vote on June 23, 2016, in favor of leaving the European Union, the landslide victory of Boris Johnson in Thursday’s election may be the most stunning. It also should have been the most predictable. After three and a half years of debilitating debate, the British had simply had enough and rallied to Mr. Johnson’s unvarnished slogan, “Get Brexit Done.” They are likely to get a very different Britain in the bargain.

abstract: Erik Prince, the controversial private security executive and prominent supporter of U.S. President Donald Trump, made a secret visit to Venezuela last month and met Vice President Delcy Rodriguez, one of socialist leader Nicolas Maduro's closest and most outspoken allies, according to five sources familiar with the matter.
snippet: Erik Prince, the controversial private security executive and prominent supporter of U.S. President Donald Trump, made a secret visit to Venezuela last month and met Vice President Delcy Rodriguez, one of socialist leader Nicolas Maduro's closest ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Erik Prince, the controversial private security executive and prominent supporter of U.S. President Donald Trump, made a secret visit to Venezuela last month and met Vice President Delcy Rodriguez, one of socialist leader Nicolas Maduro's closest and most outspoken allies, according to five sources familiar with the matter.
headline_main: Blackwater Founder Erik Prince Held Secret Talks With Top Venezuelan Official-Sources
headline_print_headline: Blackwater Founder Erik Prince Held Secret Talks With Top Venezuelan Official-Sources

abstract: When Disney bought Lucasfilm for more than $4 billion in 2012, there were lofty expectations of reviving “Star Wars” in spectacular hyper-speed fashion with a new trilogy that continued the story of Luke Skywalker and other beloved characters.
snippet: When Disney bought Lucasfilm for more than $4 billion in 2012, there were lofty expectations of reviving “Star Wars” in spectacular hyper-speed fashion with a new trilogy that continued the story of Luke Skywalker and other beloved characters.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — When Disney bought Lucasfilm for more than $4 billion in 2012, there were lofty expectations of reviving “Star Wars” in spectacular hyper-speed fashion with a new trilogy that continued the story of Luke Skywalker and other beloved characters.
headline_main: ‘Rise of Skywalker’ Is Almost Here, but a Dark Side Looms

abstract: Human rights monitors accuse the police of torture, sexual violence and other abuse, drawing scrutiny to Chile’s scandal-plagued national force.
snippet: Human rights monitors accuse the police of torture, sexual violence and other abuse, drawing scrutiny to Chile’s scandal-plagued national force.
lead_paragraph: SANTIAGO, Chile — The brutality of the Chilean police’s response to the country’s unrest  is leading to sweeping calls for the force’s reform.

abstract: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson told Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon on Friday he would not support her plan for a second independence referendum, clashing just hours after the two leaders emerged triumphant from a national election.
snippet: British Prime Minister Boris Johnson told Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon on Friday he would not support her plan for a second independence referendum, clashing just hours after the two leaders emerged triumphant from a national election.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — British Prime Minister Boris Johnson told Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon on Friday he would not support her plan for a second independence referendum, clashing just hours after the two leaders emerged triumphant from a national election.
headline_main: UK's Johnson Says No to Sturgeon's Scottish Referendum Demand
headline_print_headline: UK's Johnson Says No to Sturgeon's Scottish Referendum Demand

abstract: The U.S. House of Representatives will take up impeachment charges against President Donald Trump next week after the House Judiciary Committee on Friday recommended two charges, abuse of power and obstruction of Congress, to the full chamber.
snippet: The U.S. House of Representatives will take up impeachment charges against President Donald Trump next week after the House Judiciary Committee on Friday recommended two charges, abuse of power and obstruction of Congress, to the full chamber.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The U.S. House of Representatives will take up impeachment charges against President Donald Trump next week after the House Judiciary Committee on Friday recommended two charges, abuse of power and obstruction of Congress, to the full chamber.
headline_main: Factbox: Trump Impeachment Trial-What Happens Next?
headline_print_headline: Factbox: Trump Impeachment Trial-What Happens Next?
